Place shrimp and marinade in a recloseable food storage bag; seal. Refrigerate several hours. Prepare rice according to package directions. Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine pineapple, onion, pepper, juice from 1/2 the lime and 1/4 cup cilantro. Set aside. Prepare grill to medium-hot heat. Remove shrimp from marinade; discard marinade. Place shrimp on grill. Grill 10 minutes, turning once, or until shrimp is opaque. Toss cooked rice with juice from remaining 1/2 lime and remaining 1/4 cup cilantro. Serve shrimp over rice with pineapple salsa.